      <description>&lt;p&gt;Back in 2022 I wrote a blog post &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.devjev.nl/posts/2022/i-am-in-your-pipeline-reading-all-your-secrets/&#34;target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;external nofollow noopener noreferrer&#34;&gt;I am in your pipeline reading all your secrets!&lt;/a&gt; about how secrets can be leaked in &lt;code&gt;Azure Pipelines&lt;/code&gt;.&#xA;I think it&amp;rsquo;s time to offset that blog post and have a look at how compliance of all pipelines in a single &lt;a href=&#34;https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/devops/organizations/projects/create-project?view=azure-devops&amp;amp;tabs=browser&#34;target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;external nofollow noopener noreferrer&#34;&gt;Azure DevOps Project&lt;/a&gt; can be achieved. This is done by using a feature called &lt;a href=&#34;https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/devops/extend/develop/add-pipeline-decorator?view=azure-devops&amp;amp;wt.mc_id=DT-MVP-5005327&#34;target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;external nofollow noopener noreferrer&#34;&gt;Pipeline Decorators&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
